{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"slug":1,"metadata":2,"images":104,"html":195,"xml":246},"ISic001851",{"file":1,"uri":1,"title":3,"status":4,"editions":6,"editionAuthor":17,"type":18,"support":22,"objectType":23,"material":27,"condition":36,"dimensions":38,"layoutDesc":49,"handNote":58,"date":74,"places":78,"geo":88,"country":83,"provenance":80,"provenanceFound":92,"provenanceGeo":97,"provenanceObserved":98,"provenanceLost":17,"graphics":104,"region":117,"settlement":118,"repository":119,"idno":132,"textLang":135,"bibliographyEdition":139,"bibliographyDiscussion":155,"citation":158,"tmNumber":145,"facsimile":173,"letterHeights":174,"publications":178,"zotero":180,"keywords":182,"lettering_types":194},"Epitaph for Seilba[--]",{"_":5},"edited",[7,9,11,13,15],{"type":8},"TM",{"type":10},"EDR",{"type":12},"EDH",{"type":14},"EDCS",{"type":16},"PHI",null,{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html","Fragment of a white marble plaque, intact on the left but broken on the other three sides. The rear is finished smooth.",{"_":24,"ana":25,"ref":26},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":28,"ana":29,"type":30,"subtype":31,"resp":34,"ref":35},"Fine-grained, homogeneous, white, calcitic marble, likely Parian-1, Ephesian_white. Optical microscopy: heteroblastic to homeoblastic fabric with triple points, mosaic microstructure. Digital microscopy: heteroblastic to homeoblastic fabric. no overlap in isotopes but mgs has no match (identification based on pXRF, digital microscopy, XRD, optical microscopy, stable isotopes analysis, EPR, LA-ICP-MS)","#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Parian-1 #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Ephesian_white","stone.marble",[32,33],"Parian-1","Ephesian_white","#Coccato","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"ana":37},"#condition.fragment",[39,43,46],{"_":40,"unit":41,"dimension":42},"12.3","cm","height",{"_":44,"unit":41,"dimension":45},"18.2","width",{"_":47,"unit":41,"dimension":48},"2.5-3.3","depth",{"layout":50},{"p":51,"rs":52,"damage":56},"Remains of four lines of Greek letters, set within guidelines, which provide a border above and below each line, ignored by the letters of line 2. Consistent left margin, except for line 2 which may have been centred.",{"_":53,"ana":54,"ref":55},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":57},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":59,"dimensions":60},"Very regular v-cut letters with terminal serifs. Alpha with straight bar; quadrate epsilon, equal horizontals; standard sigma.",[61,70],{"type":62,"l":63,"from":64,"to":65,"h":66,"unit":67,"atLeast":68,"atMost":69},"letterHeight","Line 1-3","line1","line3","22-26","mm","22","26",{"type":71,"l":72,"from":64,"to":73,"unit":67},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":75,"notBefore":76,"notAfter":77},"1st — 3rd century CE",1,300,[79,84],{"_":80,"type":81,"ref":82,"region":83},"Centuripae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153","Sicilia",{"_":85,"type":86,"ref":87,"region":83},"Centuripe","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525032",[89],[90,91],37.62336,14.74049,{"_":93,"type":94,"subtype":95,"notAfter":96,"geo":17},"Part of material seized by the local inspector, L. Scavone-Campagna, in March 1912, found in illegal excavations in contrada Difesa, above 'fondo Casino'.","found","discovered","1912",[],{"_":99,"type":100,"subtype":101,"resp":102,"xml:id":103,"geo":17},"Prag  2016-06-29","observed","autopsied","#JP","autopsy",[105,112],{"n":106,"url":107,"height":108,"width":109,"desc":110,"surfaceType":111},"screen","ISic001851_tiled.tif","1978px","3000px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29","front",{"n":106,"url":113,"height":114,"width":115,"desc":110,"surfaceType":116},"ISic001851_rear_tiled.tif","1823px","2880px","rear","Sicily","Siracusa",{"_":120,"role":121,"ref":122,"museum":123},"Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097",{"slug":124,"type":121,"name":120,"uri":122,"description":125,"location":126},"097","An outstanding collection of archaeological material. The collection ranges from Siracusa and the surrounding territory (Megara Hyblaia, Akrai, Kasmenai etc) to encompass all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":118,"region":118,"country":127,"address":128,"geo":129},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":130,"lon":131},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":133,"type":134},"33026","inventory",{"_":136,"mainLang":137,"languages":138},"Ancient Greek","grc",[136],{"type":140,"bibl":141},"edition",[142],{"type":143,"n":144,"author":145,"title":146,"date":147,"citedRange":148,"ptr":149,"ref":150,"inscriptionDate":151,"citation":152,"uri":153,"year":154},"bulletin","NSA","","Notizie degli scavi di antichità","1876-","230",{"target":150},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV","1915","\u003Cspan>Accademia nazionale dei Lincei, Istituto nazionale di archeologia e storia dell’arte (Italy), e Reale Accademia d’Italia, «Notizie degli scavi di antichità», \u003Ci>Notizie degli Scavi di Antichità\u003C/i>, 1876, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/4MCP2PVV","1876",{"type":156,"bibl":157},"discussion",[17],{"editor":159,"principal":161,"contributors":162,"change":170},{"_":160,"ref":102},"Jonathan Prag",{"_":160,"ref":102},[163,166],{"_":160,"xml:id":164,"ref":165},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":167,"xml:id":168,"ref":169},"Alessia Coccato","Coccato","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820",{"_":171,"when":172,"who":102},"Jonathan Prag created file from autopsy","2025-08-07",{"n":106,"url":107,"height":108,"width":109,"desc":110,"surfaceType":111},[175],{"atLeast":176,"atMost":177},22,26,[179],"Notizie degli scavi di antichità, 1876-",[181],"4MCP2PVV",[183,184,185,19,24,186,187,188,189,190,191,192,193,137],"isic001851","epitaph for seilba[--]",{"_":5},"fine-grained, homogeneous, white, calcitic marble, likely parian-1, ephesian_white. optical microscopy: heteroblastic to homeoblastic fabric with triple points, mosaic microstructure. digital microscopy: heteroblastic to homeoblastic fabric. no overlap in isotopes but mgs has no match (identification based on pxrf, digital microscopy, xrd, optical microscopy, stable isotopes analysis, epr, la-icp-ms)","centuripae","centuripe","sicilia","sicily","siracusa","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","ancient greek",[],{"title":196,"body":197,"divs":198,"editions":223,"images":233,"handnote":244},"ISic001851. Epitaph for Seilba[--]","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ἔζησες \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> [ἔτη] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.3)\u003C/span> · κη´ · [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">Σειλβα[νὸς?]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>χρη̣[στέ \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al0-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΕΖΗΣΕΣ&nbsp;&nbsp;[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;·ΚΗ·[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">ΣΕΙΛΒΑ[...]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΧΡ.[...\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ΣΗ; it is unlikely there is any text missing from the rest of line 2.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ΣΕΙΑΒΛ[---];The space after Α probably reflects the increasing spacing of the letters to fill the line, rather than an actual vacat; the cross bar of the alpha is visible on the break\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[...] you lived 28 years. Seilbanos (Silvanus), worthy one[...]\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>It seems likely that approximately 2/3 of the width of the stone is preserved, with room for 3-4 letters in the missing right portion - this is suggested most directly by lines 1-2, where the only word missing must be ἔτη, followed by the age in line 2 which has apparently been centred. Missing from the top of the stone would be the name of the deceased, followed most likely by χρηστέ χαῖρε (cf. e.g. ISic001397). In line 3, the presence of a name, followed in line 4 by the beginnings of χρηστέ implies that we have a second epitaph, rather than a record of the person who was responsible for the initial epitaph. Σειλβα[---] is probably a Greek transliteration of the Latin name Silvanus, which may or may not have here been written in the vocative.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1915 230 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Very regular v-cut letters with terminal serifs. Alpha with straight bar; quadrate epsilon, equal horizontals; standard sigma.\u003C/p> Line 1-3  22-26  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[199,202,205,208,211,214,217,220],{"id":200,"html":201},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ἔζησες \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> [ἔτη] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.3)\u003C/span> · κη´ · [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">Σειλβα[νὸς?]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>χρη̣[στέ \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al0-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΕΖΗΣΕΣ&nbsp;&nbsp;[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;·ΚΗ·[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">ΣΕΙΛΒΑ[...]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΧΡ.[...\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":203,"html":204},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001851_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\" src=\"ISic001851_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":206,"html":207},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ΣΗ; it is unlikely there is any text missing from the rest of line 2.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ΣΕΙΑΒΛ[---];The space after Α probably reflects the increasing spacing of the letters to fill the line, rather than an actual vacat; the cross bar of the alpha is visible on the break\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":209,"html":210},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[...] you lived 28 years. Seilbanos (Silvanus), worthy one[...]\u003C/p>  ",{"id":212,"html":213},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>It seems likely that approximately 2/3 of the width of the stone is preserved, with room for 3-4 letters in the missing right portion - this is suggested most directly by lines 1-2, where the only word missing must be ἔτη, followed by the age in line 2 which has apparently been centred. Missing from the top of the stone would be the name of the deceased, followed most likely by χρηστέ χαῖρε (cf. e.g. ISic001397). In line 3, the presence of a name, followed in line 4 by the beginnings of χρηστέ implies that we have a second epitaph, rather than a record of the person who was responsible for the initial epitaph. Σειλβα[---] is probably a Greek transliteration of the Latin name Silvanus, which may or may not have here been written in the vocative.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":215,"html":216},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1915 230 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":218,"html":219},"handnote","\u003Cp>Very regular v-cut letters with terminal serifs. Alpha with straight bar; quadrate epsilon, equal horizontals; standard sigma.\u003C/p> Line 1-3  22-26  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":221,"html":222},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[224,226,229,230],{"html":225},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-06-29",{"id":227,"lang":137,"html":228},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ἔζησες \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> [ἔτη] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.3)\u003C/span> · κη´ · [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">Σειλβα[νὸς?]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>χρη̣[στέ \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":225},{"id":231,"lang":137,"html":232},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al0-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΕΖΗΣΕΣ&nbsp;&nbsp;[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;·ΚΗ·[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σειλβανὸς\">ΣΕΙΛΒΑ[...]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΧΡ.[...\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[234,236,239,241],{"image":107,"thumb":235,"title":110},"ISic001851_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":237,"thumb":238,"title":110},"ISic001851.jpg","ISic001851-thumb.jpg",{"image":113,"thumb":240,"title":110},"ISic001851_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":242,"thumb":243,"title":110},"ISic001851_rear.jpg","ISic001851_rear-thumb.jpg",[245],{"html":59},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Epitaph for Seilba[--]\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n             \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic001851\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001851\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Siracusa\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097\">Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">33026\u003C/idno>\u003C!-- also, subsequently given the number 102147 ? -->\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Fragment of a white marble plaque, intact on the left but broken on the other three sides. The rear is finished smooth.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">12.3\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">18.2\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">2.5-3.3\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.fragment\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Remains of four lines of Greek letters, set within guidelines, which provide a border above and below each line, ignored by the letters of line 2. Consistent left margin, except for line 2 which may have been centred.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Very regular v-cut letters with terminal serifs. Alpha with straight bar; quadrate epsilon, equal horizontals; standard sigma.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line3\">Line 1-3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"22\" atMost=\"26\">22-26\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153\">Centuripae\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525032\">Centuripe\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.62336, 14.74049\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0001\" notAfter-custom=\"0300\">1st — 3rd century CE\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" notAfter=\"1912\">Part of material seized by the local inspector, L. Scavone-Campagna, in March 1912, found in illegal excavations in contrada Difesa, above 'fondo Casino'.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" resp=\"#JP\" xml:id=\"autopsy\">Prag  2016-06-29\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2025-08-07\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created file from autopsy\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001851_tiled.tif\" height=\"1978px\" width=\"3000px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001851.jpg\" height=\"1978px\" width=\"3000px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"rear\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001851_rear_tiled.tif\" height=\"1823px\" width=\"2880px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001851_rear.jpg\" height=\"1823px\" width=\"2880px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-29\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n        \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\" source=\"#autopsy\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"0\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" unit=\"character\" extent=\"unknown\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>ἔζησες \u003Cspace unit=\"character\" quantity=\"1\"/> \u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">ἔτη\u003C/supplied>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cspace unit=\"character\" quantity=\"3\"/> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cnum value=\"28\">κη\u003C/num> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Σειλβα\u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\" cert=\"low\">νὸς\u003C/supplied>\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>χρ\u003Cunclear>η\u003C/unclear>\u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">στέ\u003C/supplied> \u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" unit=\"character\" extent=\"unknown\"/>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>text from autopsy\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"2\">\u003Cnote>Orsi: ΣΗ; it is unlikely there is any text missing from the rest of line 2.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"3\">\u003Cnote>Orsi: ΣΕΙΑΒΛ[---];The space after Α probably reflects the increasing spacing of the letters to fill the line, rather than an actual vacat; the cross bar of the alpha is visible on the break\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>[...] you lived 28 years. Seilbanos (Silvanus), worthy one[...]\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>It seems likely that approximately 2/3 of the width of the stone is preserved, with room for 3-4 letters in the missing right portion - this is suggested most directly by lines 1-2, where the only word missing must be ἔτη, followed by the age in line 2 which has apparently been centred. Missing from the top of the stone would be the name of the deceased, followed most likely by χρηστέ χαῖρε (cf. e.g. ISic001397).  In line 3, the presence of a name, followed in line 4 by the beginnings of χρηστέ implies that we have a second epitaph, rather than a record of the person who was responsible for the initial epitaph. Σειλβα[---] is probably a Greek transliteration of the Latin name Silvanus, which may or may not have here been written in the vocative.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"NSA\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Orsi\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Ctitle>NSA\u003C/title>\n                        \u003Cdate>1915\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>230\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                   \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
